Go where. go?

251
00:16:24.980 --> 00:16:26.640
Home. Molly.

252
00:16:26.710 --> 00:16:29.650
The place where I live.
where I have a life.

253
00:16:29.720 --> 00:16:33.120
where I do my laundry.
get sleep. try to make music.

254
00:16:33.190 --> 00:16:35.090
Why can't you
make music here?

255
00:16:35.160 --> 00:16:37.150
This is a world gone mad.

256
00:16:37.220 --> 00:16:39.320
like I've stepped
through the looking-glass.

257
00:16:39.390 --> 00:16:42.120
There's a week's worth of leftovers.
a month of laundry.

258
00:16:42.200 --> 00:16:44.630
Look at this place.
- We'll call maid service.

259
00:16:44.700 --> 00:16:48.930
You call maid service.
I've got to rejoin the human race.

260
00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:50.200
No!

261
00:16:53.040 --> 00:16:54.200
I don't understand.

262
00:16:54.270 --> 00:16:58.440
Listen. I just feel
like I'm suffocating.

263
00:16:58.510 --> 00:17:01.500
I need some air.
- We can open the windows.

264
00:17:01.580 --> 00:17:05.250
It's not about the windows.
I need my shirt back.

265
00:17:07.650 --> 00:17:09.880
Damn! I forgot
to get new strings.

266
00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:12.390
I have. like.
five gigs this week

267
00:17:12.460 --> 00:17:15.360
and I have not done
a single thing.

268
00:17:15.430 --> 00:17:19.630
I have got to get to work.
I'll call you later. I swear.

269
00:17:31.380 --> 00:17:33.510
Oh. my God.

270
00:17:33.580 --> 00:17:36.070
This place is beyond
its normal grotesque.

271
00:17:36.150 --> 00:17:37.780
It's post-nuclear.

272
00:17:40.150 --> 00:17:42.780
Ninety-eight messages?

273
00:17:42.860 --> 00:17:46.120
Molly. your machine
has 98 messages on it.

274
00:17:46.190 --> 00:17:48.420
Write them down for me.
will you?

275
00:17:49.800 --> 00:17:53.430
He's gone.
I have no life.

276
00:17:56.870 --> 00:17:58.100
What?

277
00:17:58.170 --> 00:18:00.570
"Of course you have a life."

278
00:18:01.310 --> 00:18:03.300
"I don't need to tell you that."

279
00:18:03.380 --> 00:18:05.370
That's what you're
supposed to say to me.

280
00:18:05.450 --> 00:18:06.470
Sorry.

281
00:18:06.550 --> 00:18:10.070
As your best friend.
it's my duty not to lie to you.

282
00:18:10.150 --> 00:18:12.880
Besides.
you wanted him gone. remember?

283
00:18:12.950 --> 00:18:14.820
I did?

284
00:18:15.960 --> 00:18:17.790
What are all these
final notices?

285
00:18:17.860 --> 00:18:19.690
I'm gonna call him.

286
00:18:19.760 --> 00:18:21.990
I think now is
a good time to call him.

287
00:18:23.030 --> 00:18:25.400
Would you hand me the phone?
I'm gonna call him right now.

288
00:18:27.130 --> 00:18:29.860
Focus for one second.

289
00:18:29.940 --> 00:18:33.930
Your electric has been canceled
and so has your gas.

290
00:18:34.010 --> 00:18:36.070
Who pays your bills?

291
00:18:37.080 --> 00:18:38.310
Bob.

292
00:18:39.550 --> 00:18:40.980
Bob who?

293
00:18:41.050 --> 00:18:43.640
I don't know.
My parents' guy Bob.

294
00:18:49.460 --> 00:18:51.250
Your phone's dead.

295
00:18:51.330 --> 00:18:53.190
These rooms...

296
00:18:54.800 --> 00:18:58.820
sound so empty
without the sound of his music.

297
00:19:00.770 --> 00:19:03.460
Bob's number
has been disconnected.

298
00:19:04.470 --> 00:19:05.600
Oh. God.

299
00:19:05.670 --> 00:19:08.510
I'm sure it's little consolation.
but you're not the only one

300
00:19:08.580 --> 00:19:10.480
who got taken. Miss Gunn.

301
00:19:10.540 --> 00:19:13.240
Bob Kopalski had ten clients.

302
00:19:13.310 --> 00:19:16.940
assets equaling over $100 million.
when he disappeared.

303
00:19:17.020 --> 00:19:19.250
You're telling us
that none of it's insured?

304
00:19:19.320 --> 00:19:23.020
What a disaster.
Thank God for the residuals.

305
00:19:23.090 --> 00:19:28.080
Actually. Kopalski took such heavy
advances on the royalty income

306
00:19:28.160 --> 00:19:31.130
that by the time
the account recoups.

307
00:19:31.200 --> 00:19:33.460
Miss Gunn will be
on Social Security.

308
00:19:33.530 --> 00:19:36.440
Where does someone disappear
with $100 million?

309
00:19:36.500 --> 00:19:39.560
The best we can guess
is South America.

310
00:19:39.640 --> 00:19:41.130
Can't you just sue?

311
00:19:41.210 --> 00:19:45.010
My God.
how could he do this to her?

312
00:19:45.080 --> 00:19:48.610
He'll be back.
They always come back.

313
00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:52.170
If he does. he'll be looking
out the back of an FBI van

314
00:19:52.250 --> 00:19:54.480
on his way
to a long prison term.

315
00:19:54.560 --> 00:19:58.550
It'll be years
before you see a dime. if ever.

316
00:20:00.530 --> 00:20:05.060
Mr. Feldman. as a lawyer.

317
00:20:05.130 --> 00:20:07.400
may I please ask your advice

318
00:20:07.470 --> 00:20:12.960
as per what to do in the meantime
as far as. you know. money?

319
00:20:14.270 --> 00:20:15.830
Get a job?

320
00:20:18.450 --> 00:20:19.880
"Dear prospective employer.

321
00:20:20.210 --> 00:20:22.650
"although I've had
no previous employment. ever.

322
00:20:22.720 --> 00:20:24.950
"the following is a partial
but significant list

323
00:20:25.020 --> 00:20:28.950
of personal recommendations.
including contact information."

324
00:20:29.820 --> 00:20:32.550
The Dalai Lama. Tibet?

325
00:20:32.630 --> 00:20:35.960
900-thread count
Egyptian cotton.

326
00:20:36.730 --> 00:20:40.360
No man can resist
Egyptian cotton.

327
00:20:40.430 --> 00:20:43.340
Tibet is a country. Molly.
not contact information.

328
00:20:43.400 --> 00:20:44.890
Why not add "earth"

329
00:20:44.970 --> 00:20:47.170
in case someone
needs to know where Tibet is?

330
00:20:47.240 --> 00:20:48.970
This is not a résumé.

331
00:20:49.040 --> 00:20:51.310
It shows I'm a people person.

332
00:20:53.350 --> 00:20:54.840
Focus on the interview.

333
00:20:54.920 --> 00:20:56.910
Hello.
Pleasure to meet you.

334
00:20:56.980 --> 00:21:00.080
I will work overtime. weekends.
holidays. Yom Kippur. Christmas.

335
00:21:00.150 --> 00:21:03.250
You name it. I will be here.
- I'm sure that won't be necessary.

336
00:21:03.320 --> 00:21:05.690
Ingrid says you guys met
at Darlington?

337
00:21:05.760 --> 00:21:08.590
I was valedictorian there
two years in a row.

338
00:21:08.660 --> 00:21:10.960
That's so neat.

339
00:21:11.300 --> 00:21:14.430
Tell me. what is the price
on a set of these?

340
00:21:14.500 --> 00:21:17.560
$1.369 plus tax.

341
00:21:17.640 --> 00:21:20.940
You're in denial.
You're broke. remember?

342
00:21:21.010 --> 00:21:25.070
Trish. hon. tell me. do employees
get a discount around here?

343
00:21:25.150 --> 00:21:29.170
Ten percent. and some employees
are among our best customers.

344
00:21:32.020 --> 00:21:36.550
I'll take them.
Ing. this is the greatest job ever.

345
00:21:44.100 --> 00:21:47.330
Who is it?
- It's Molly!

346
00:21:47.400 --> 00:21:50.460
I was just out shopping
in the neighborhood.

347
00:21:50.540 --> 00:21:53.940
At midnight?
- It's the city that never sleeps.

348
00:21:57.740 --> 00:22:00.870
You can't do this.
I have to be at the studio at 9:00.

349
00:22:00.950 --> 00:22:03.680
I can't act like a kid anymore.
- Really?

350
00:22:03.750 --> 00:22:07.410
Neal. I haven't seen sheets
like this since the third grade.

351
00:22:08.960 --> 00:22:10.290
Rocket ships?

352
00:22:10.360 --> 00:22:13.760
You wouldn't have my jacket in there?
It's like my lucky jacket.

353
00:22:13.830 --> 00:22:17.260
I never get onstage without it.
I left it behind the other day.

354
00:22:17.330 --> 00:22:18.960
No.

355
00:22:19.030 --> 00:22:22.800
I guess you're gonna have to
come over and look for it.

356
00:22:22.870 --> 00:22:25.300
I can't disappear
from the world again.

357
00:22:25.370 --> 00:22:29.310
I can't lose myself in this obsessive-
compulsive irrational behavior.

358
00:22:34.680 --> 00:22:36.010
Feel.

359
00:22:36.680 --> 00:22:38.580
Excuse me?
- Feel.

360
00:22:40.850 --> 00:22:42.850
Egyptian cotton...

361
00:22:44.390 --> 00:22:46.880
900-thread count.

362
00:22:48.760 --> 00:22:50.750
All right. I'll tell you what.

363
00:22:50.830 --> 00:22:54.160
Maybe we can. like.
date. okay?

364
00:22:54.230 --> 00:22:55.220
Okay.

365
00:22:55.300 --> 00:23:00.070
But it's gonna have to be
a mature adult relationship with...

366
00:23:00.140 --> 00:23:02.840
alarm clocks in the morning...
- I love alarm clocks.

367
00:23:02.910 --> 00:23:05.070
and work during the day.

368
00:23:05.150 --> 00:23:08.340
We eat with silverware.
knives and forks...

369
00:23:09.080 --> 00:23:10.980
drink out of glasses...

370
00:23:11.620 --> 00:23:13.210
do the dishes.

371
00:23:14.420 --> 00:23:16.410
Is it bedtime yet?

372
00:23:21.400 --> 00:23:23.420
Molly. wake up.

373
00:23:29.540 --> 00:23:31.060
I'm sorry.

374
00:23:31.710 --> 00:23:33.760
It's not going to work out.

375
00:23:34.610 --> 00:23:37.740
You spent all night at that guy's
house doing God knows what.

376
00:23:37.810 --> 00:23:39.840
then you come here
and crash at work.

377
00:23:39.910 --> 00:23:43.680
I can't believe you did this to me
after all the strings I pulled.

378
00:23:43.750 --> 00:23:46.410
I know that I'm
an undeserving creep.

379
00:23:46.490 --> 00:23:48.820
but can we please
talk about it over lunch?

380
00:23:48.890 --> 00:23:52.090
No! Our lunch date is canceled.
You can't afford lunch.

381
00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:56.360
Fine. see if I care.
I'll live off of water and sunshine.

382
00:23:56.430 --> 00:23:58.090
You won't have to.

383
00:23:58.170 --> 00:24:01.230
Once again your main man
is gonna come through for ya.

384
00:24:02.770 --> 00:24:05.740
You're gonna get me
a record deal.

385
00:24:05.810 --> 00:24:07.360
Not exactly.

386
00:24:17.820 --> 00:24:21.780
Hi!
- Oh. my God.

387
00:24:21.860 --> 00:24:23.650
You're my new nanny?

388
00:24:23.720 --> 00:24:25.850
Hi. Laraine.
- It's Ray.

389
00:24:26.860 --> 00:24:28.560
Nobody calls me Laraine.

390
00:24:28.630 --> 00:24:31.190
Okay. Ray. I'm Molly.

391
00:24:31.260 --> 00:24:33.260
We met at my birthday party.
remember?

392
00:24:33.330 --> 00:24:34.490
You're late.

393
00:24:34.570 --> 00:24:36.090
By. like. a second.

394
00:24:36.800 --> 00:24:39.800
By three and a half minutes.

395
00:24:39.870 --> 00:24:45.330
I have to take my Aciphex
by 4:26. and it's...4:18 right now.

396
00:24:45.410 --> 00:24:48.970
We'll take it when we get home.
- That's when I take my Colitin.

397
00:24:51.120 --> 00:24:53.450
The agency must really be
getting desperate.

398
00:24:54.120 --> 00:24:56.820
I actually am uniquely qualified
for this position.

399
00:24:56.890 --> 00:24:58.720
having spent so many years

400
00:24:58.790 --> 00:25:01.230
developing my skills
as a people person.

401
00:25:10.200 --> 00:25:12.230
Mission accomplished?

402
00:25:12.310 --> 00:25:14.100
Fruit punch?

403
00:25:14.170 --> 00:25:16.610
Why don't you
just drink cyanide?

404
00:25:16.680 --> 00:25:18.230
At least it's quick.

405
00:25:22.820 --> 00:25:23.940
Damn.

406
00:25:24.680 --> 00:25:26.850
Hang your coat up in there.

407
00:26:20.070 --> 00:26:22.230
What is this. The Shining?

408
00:26:42.900 --> 00:26:44.960
Who is that?
- Nobody.

409
00:26:46.600 --> 00:26:49.470
What's wrong with him?
- None of your b-i business.

410
00:26:49.540 --> 00:26:50.940
Shoes!

411
00:27:02.680 --> 00:27:04.740
This is your room?

412
00:27:04.820 --> 00:27:07.290
There's no fooling you.
is there?

413
00:27:09.220 --> 00:27:10.520
It's so...

414
00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:17.150
orderly.

415
00:27:20.730 --> 00:27:22.220
These are so neat!

416
00:27:22.300 --> 00:27:24.400
I remember when there were
only four models.

417
00:27:24.470 --> 00:27:27.410
I can't believe this.
She's beautiful.

418
00:27:27.470 --> 00:27:29.940
Look at these legs.
- That's Pliéing Polly.

419
00:27:30.010 --> 00:27:32.040
Put her back!

420
00:27:35.750 --> 00:27:37.770
How cool is this?

421
00:27:37.850 --> 00:27:39.880
Look at this little tea set!

422
00:27:42.920 --> 00:27:46.820
You don't touch that unless
I happen to invite you to tea.

423
00:27:46.890 --> 00:27:48.920
Look at these cute little scones.

424
00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:50.990
Get away from there.

425
00:27:51.060 --> 00:27:55.260
Well. I say. Lady Sassafras.
would you like some crème fraîche

426
00:27:55.340 --> 00:27:57.900
to go with
your darling pastries?

427
00:28:00.710 --> 00:28:05.800
You just got your germy drool
over my plastic scone. you freako.

428
00:28:12.420 --> 00:28:14.720
Kid. have you ever been
to a shrink?

429
00:28:14.790 --> 00:28:16.150
Since I was three.

430
00:28:18.360 --> 00:28:19.350
What?

431
00:28:19.430 --> 00:28:22.860
Good afternoon. Miss Ray.
Dinner is ready.

432
00:28:24.630 --> 00:28:27.600
There's just nothing
like good help.

433
00:28:36.880 --> 00:28:38.500
You missed a spot.

434
00:28:40.110 --> 00:28:43.240
Isn't doing the dishes what the maid
is supposed to be for?

435
00:28:43.320 --> 00:28:45.650
She doesn't know how to dry
without leaving spots.

436
00:28:45.720 --> 00:28:48.380
You don't know how to dry
without destroying the environment.

437
00:28:48.460 --> 00:28:50.620
For every roll
of paper towels you waste.

438
00:28:50.690 --> 00:28:52.680
a tree in the rain forest dies.

439
00:28:52.760 --> 00:28:54.250
I'm gonna die of botulism

440
00:28:54.330 --> 00:28:56.990
from the germs on that gunky
towel. you tree-loving hippie.

441
00:28:57.060 --> 00:29:01.360
At least I don't prefer tofu
to normal hamburgers.

442
00:29:01.430 --> 00:29:04.670
I'm not the one who's gonna get
mad cow disease and go nuts.

443
00:29:04.740 --> 00:29:07.610
though you don't seem to have
a brain to fry in the first place.

444
00:29:07.670 --> 00:29:11.700
Maybe not. but at least I'm not
holding the germ-infested towel.

445
00:29:14.980 --> 00:29:16.110
Give me that plate.

446
00:29:16.180 --> 00:29:18.170
No. sorry.
You might infect it.

447
00:29:19.250 --> 00:29:22.550
Why don't you get your plastic
baggie and dig up some penicillin?

448
00:29:22.620 --> 00:29:24.090
No!
- Come on.

449
00:29:24.160 --> 00:29:26.390
Give me the plate!
- You want it?

450
00:29:26.460 --> 00:29:27.650
How bad do you want it?

451
00:29:31.800 --> 00:29:33.460
Get a broom.

452
00:29:33.530 --> 00:29:36.160
You get a frickin' broom.

453
00:29:37.540 --> 00:29:40.770
When you work for me.
you leave when I say you can leave.

454
00:29:40.840 --> 00:29:43.470
For your information.
I do not work for you.

455
00:29:43.540 --> 00:29:45.370
I am employed by your mother.

456
00:29:45.450 --> 00:29:48.040
Yeah?
Take a look around.

457
00:29:48.110 --> 00:29:50.110
Do you see her anywhere?

458
00:29:50.180 --> 00:29:53.640
News flash... you're not gonna

459
00:29:53.720 --> 00:29:56.050
unless you make an appointment
with her assistant

460
00:29:56.120 --> 00:29:59.110
or hang around her bedroom door
at 3:00 in the morning.

461
00:29:59.190 --> 00:30:04.220
In the meantime.
you're workin' for me.

462
00:30:04.300 --> 00:30:06.490
Is that so?

463
00:30:07.900 --> 00:30:11.930
News flash. Mussolini...

464
00:30:13.370 --> 00:30:14.860
I quit!

465
00:30:20.450 --> 00:30:23.610
Are you all right. Miss Gunn?
- Just great.

466
00:30:31.990 --> 00:30:33.550
Baby!

467
00:30:34.260 --> 00:30:37.700
Baby. what are you doing outside
all by yourself?

468
00:30:40.330 --> 00:30:43.130
How did you get locked out?

469
00:30:45.670 --> 00:30:47.660
Mama's had a day.

470
00:30:55.350 --> 00:30:59.510
I've lived here for 20 years.
How can you do this?

471
00:30:59.590 --> 00:31:01.520
Aside from that...

472
00:31:03.120 --> 00:31:05.280
This is a family building.
Miss Gunn.

473
00:31:05.360 --> 00:31:08.290
I suggest you find somewhere
you'd be more welcome.

474
00:31:08.360 --> 00:31:10.300
Like Los Angeles.

475
00:31:10.360 --> 00:31:12.350
You will be allowed back
into your apartment

476
00:31:12.430 --> 00:31:15.730
only so long as you are accompanied
by a management representative

477
00:31:15.800 --> 00:31:18.330
and only long enough
to gather your belongings.

478
00:31:18.400 --> 00:31:21.740
That is. those personal belongings
we don't insist on holding

479
00:31:21.810 --> 00:31:25.900
as collateral for the rent
and utilities you owe.

480
00:31:25.980 --> 00:31:29.470
You are otherwise barred
from the premises.

481
00:31:58.380 --> 00:32:00.440
I know this is
a big change for you.

482
00:32:00.510 --> 00:32:03.140
but it'll feel like home
in no time at all.

483
00:32:03.220 --> 00:32:07.020
This is the bedroom...
my bedroom. of course...

484
00:32:07.090 --> 00:32:10.020
but there's plenty
of drawer space if you need it.

485
00:32:10.090 --> 00:32:12.920
I can't believe those creeps
would throw a destitute woman

486
00:32:12.990 --> 00:32:14.480
into the street.

487
00:32:14.560 --> 00:32:16.550
Chivalry is so dead.

488
00:32:16.630 --> 00:32:19.790
This is the bathroom.
I hung up your towels for you.

489
00:32:19.870 --> 00:32:21.990
I've been here
a thousand times.

490
00:32:22.070 --> 00:32:23.560
You know the kitchen.

491
00:32:23.640 --> 00:32:27.130
Julie and Holly come over
Thursdays for our weekly bake fest.

492
00:32:27.210 --> 00:32:30.470
Mondays. Penny and Ethel come
so we can do yoga with Rajiiv

493
00:32:30.540 --> 00:32:32.410
right here in the living room.

494
00:32:32.480 --> 00:32:36.510
But this is going to be
a problem.

495
00:32:37.150 --> 00:32:41.250
Ing. don't you think it's weird
that Neal hasn't called me?

496
00:32:41.320 --> 00:32:43.980
No. but I think it's weird
that you're wearing his jacket.

497
00:32:44.060 --> 00:32:46.580
I told you just bring
the essentials. Molly.

498
00:32:46.660 --> 00:32:49.060
You can't keep all this stuff.

499
00:32:49.130 --> 00:32:52.190
And he definitely has to go.

500
00:32:57.800 --> 00:32:59.800
Mu. what are we gonna do?

501
00:32:59.870 --> 00:33:01.970
Downsize. Molly.
Purify.

502
00:33:02.040 --> 00:33:04.170
Streamline.
find your center.

503
00:33:04.240 --> 00:33:05.710
You're right. Ing.

504
00:33:05.780 --> 00:33:08.770
We're gonna get you the best
housewarming present ever.

505
00:33:08.850 --> 00:33:10.010
Don't be silly.

506
00:33:10.080 --> 00:33:13.450
It's gonna be hard enough on you
coming up with half the rent.

507
00:33:31.070 --> 00:33:33.230
Wonderful. girls.

508
00:33:33.310 --> 00:33:35.900
Tomorrow we start rehearsing
for next month's recital.

509
00:33:35.980 --> 00:33:38.000
but I think we still have
five minutes.

510
00:33:38.080 --> 00:33:40.810
How about a little freestyle?

511
00:33:47.990 --> 00:33:51.010
You sure looked great
out there.

512
00:33:54.090 --> 00:33:57.150
I just. you know...

513
00:33:57.230 --> 00:33:59.930
Yelling at you
the other day and all...

514
00:34:01.900 --> 00:34:03.490
I'm sorry.

515
00:34:05.000 --> 00:34:06.900
What are you doing here?

516
00:34:06.970 --> 00:34:09.970
I called Roma. your mom...

517
00:34:11.010 --> 00:34:15.410
and she said that if you said
that it was okay.

518
00:34:15.480 --> 00:34:17.470
I could have my job back?

519
00:34:24.260 --> 00:34:26.160
You're on probation.

520
00:34:32.030 --> 00:34:34.260
Act your age.
not your shoe size.

521
00:34:34.330 --> 00:34:36.730
How come you left
dance class so early?

522
00:34:36.800 --> 00:34:39.570
That freestyle at the end
looked like so much fun.

523
00:34:39.640 --> 00:34:43.200
Freestyle is for moronic little kids
and hippie freaks.

524
00:34:43.280 --> 00:34:45.070
It's fun.

525
00:34:45.140 --> 00:34:47.870
Fundamentals
are the building blocks of fun.

526
00:34:47.950 --> 00:34:49.070
Says who?

527
00:34:49.150 --> 00:34:53.590
Mikhail Baryshnikov.
who I'm sure you've never heard of.

528
00:34:53.650 --> 00:34:56.990
Ballet is about precision.
discipline. and poise.

529
00:34:57.060 --> 00:34:59.050
They made us take ballet
at Darlington.

530
00:34:59.130 --> 00:35:02.390
I couldn't wait to get out there
and make up all my own moves.

531
00:35:02.460 --> 00:35:04.190
Figures.
Such a sloppy doofus.

532
00:35:04.260 --> 00:35:06.750
Figures. You're such
a pill-popping little tyrant.

533
00:35:07.770 --> 00:35:09.430
Don't ever do that
to me again.

534
00:35:09.500 --> 00:35:11.600
You're hurting me.
- You hurt me.

535
00:35:11.670 --> 00:35:12.870
Take it back.

536
00:35:14.610 --> 00:35:16.070
Take it back.

537
00:35:16.610 --> 00:35:18.200
Fine.

538
00:35:19.880 --> 00:35:22.140
I take it back.

539
00:35:23.450 --> 00:35:25.380
It's a good thing you did.

540
00:35:25.450 --> 00:35:28.180
Otherwise you wouldn't
have gotten your surprise.

541
00:35:29.520 --> 00:35:30.890
Surprise.

542
00:35:30.960 --> 00:35:33.590
I really hate surprises.
and I sincerely doubt

543
00:35:33.660 --> 00:35:36.960
there's anything you could give me
that I don't already have.

544
00:35:37.030 --> 00:35:39.190
There's no harm
in trying. is there?

545
00:35:47.610 --> 00:35:49.270
Ray. are you all right?

546
00:35:52.680 --> 00:35:56.170
My glands are swollen.
I'm having an allergic reaction.

547
00:35:56.250 --> 00:35:58.240
My immune system
is crashing.

548
00:35:58.320 --> 00:36:01.080
Mu stayed with you
one measly little night.

549
00:36:01.150 --> 00:36:02.420
Come on.

550
00:36:04.290 --> 00:36:06.050
And that's all
he's gonna be staying.

551
00:36:06.130 --> 00:36:09.220
Wasn't it fun. though.
sneaking him in and out for his walk?

552
00:36:09.300 --> 00:36:12.530
It was like a real. live adventure.
You know you had fun.

553
00:36:12.600 --> 00:36:14.360
I'm not a swineherd. kook.

554
00:36:14.430 --> 00:36:16.300
Excuse me.
How much is this putter?

555
00:36:16.370 --> 00:36:19.400
This putter is not for sale.
Sorry. This is a mistake.

556
00:36:19.470 --> 00:36:22.030
You don't golf.
- Tiger gave this to me.

557
00:36:22.110 --> 00:36:24.540
Essentials. remember?
You've got to get rid of this junk.

558
00:36:24.610 --> 00:36:25.800
It's essential.

559
00:36:27.850 --> 00:36:29.470
Twenty dollars.
- Ten.

560
00:36:29.550 --> 00:36:30.680
Sold.

561
00:36:30.750 --> 00:36:33.410
Can I talk to you for a second?
Come through here.

562
00:36:33.490 --> 00:36:36.940
Do me a favor. all right?
Watch your step.

563
00:36:37.790 --> 00:36:39.880
This is Kelli.
Kelli. this is Molly.

564
00:36:39.960 --> 00:36:41.150
Pleasure to meet you.

565
00:36:41.230 --> 00:36:43.890
Looks almost as good on her
as it does on you. doesn't it?

566
00:36:43.960 --> 00:36:48.230
Gooey! Looks like Mu isn't
the only pig you hang out with.

567
00:36:48.300 --> 00:36:49.960
Go away!

568
00:36:50.040 --> 00:36:52.800
It must be really hard
getting rid of all this neat stuff.

569
00:36:52.870 --> 00:36:55.310
No. I'm actually loving it.

570
00:36:55.370 --> 00:36:57.370
Really?
- It's very refreshing.

571
00:36:57.440 --> 00:36:59.780
Everybody. once in their life.
should do this

572
00:36:59.850 --> 00:37:04.510
and slough off all the bad...
Wait!

573
00:37:04.580 --> 00:37:07.780
Sorry. This is... mine.

574
00:37:07.850 --> 00:37:11.220
No. I just bought it.
- How much did you pay?

575
00:37:11.290 --> 00:37:13.450
Thirty dollars.
- My friend Rosella gave it to me.

576
00:37:13.530 --> 00:37:15.990
I'll give you 50. 75!

577
00:37:16.760 --> 00:37:18.090
Enough!

578
00:37:18.160 --> 00:37:20.160
We're downsizing. remember?

579
00:37:20.230 --> 00:37:23.830
Sloughing off the excess
to find our center.

580
00:37:23.900 --> 00:37:25.600
You want this. Molly.

581
00:37:25.670 --> 00:37:28.370
Close your eyes
and repeat after me.

582
00:37:28.710 --> 00:37:30.510
I want this.

583
00:37:41.820 --> 00:37:43.190
Miss Gunn?

584
00:37:45.520 --> 00:37:48.020
We're ready to pack this room up
for storage. ma'am.

585
00:37:49.900 --> 00:37:52.800
Can I have just
five more minutes. please?

586
00:37:52.870 --> 00:37:54.560
Okay. sure.
- Thank you.

587
00:38:08.550 --> 00:38:10.010
Is that you?

588
00:38:17.620 --> 00:38:19.320
Dad's a rock star?

589
00:38:20.130 --> 00:38:21.390
Was.

590
00:38:22.360 --> 00:38:23.830
He's dead.

591
00:38:24.560 --> 00:38:27.900
Bet this stuff
is worth a bundle.

592
00:38:27.970 --> 00:38:30.560
I can't just sell it. Ray.

593
00:38:30.640 --> 00:38:33.660
It's my parents' stuff.

594
00:38:34.740 --> 00:38:39.010
No. you're gonna box it up so it
can lay in storage gathering dust.

595
00:38:40.510 --> 00:38:42.670
God. you're pathetic.

596
00:38:46.850 --> 00:38:49.790
That man in the library
in your house...

597
00:38:51.490 --> 00:38:55.020
nurse said he's in a coma
from a massive stroke.

598
00:38:56.000 --> 00:38:58.160
That's your father. huh?

599
00:38:59.100 --> 00:39:00.690
Was.

600
00:39:00.770 --> 00:39:02.830
He's a vegetable now.

601
00:39:02.900 --> 00:39:05.130
Soon he'll be nothing.

602
00:39:06.140 --> 00:39:08.200
That's kind of harsh.

603
00:39:10.480 --> 00:39:12.600
It's a harsh world.

604
00:39:17.780 --> 00:39:19.770
Watch where you're going!

605
00:39:34.930 --> 00:39:37.430
Neal. I really hate talking
to your machine.

606
00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:38.990
Where are you?

607
00:39:39.070 --> 00:39:41.440
I'm still holding on
to your jacket for you.

608
00:39:41.510 --> 00:39:43.910
I know you've been going crazy
trying to reach me.

609
00:39:43.980 --> 00:39:47.430
but I've been
in a transition right now.

610
00:39:47.510 --> 00:39:50.070
I'm. like. Miss Proletariat now.

611
00:39:50.150 --> 00:39:54.450
Mop the floors. spank the brat.
pick up the paycheck on Friday.

612
00:39:54.520 --> 00:39:57.220
I am a woman.
How about you?

613
00:39:57.290 --> 00:39:58.880
Shit!

614
00:40:05.730 --> 00:40:07.720
Get under the tail.

615
00:40:07.800 --> 00:40:09.890
I'm not putting my hand
under his heinie.

616
00:40:09.970 --> 00:40:11.660
Do you want him
to stay here or not?

617
00:40:11.740 --> 00:40:14.640
Oh. God!
Oh. my God!

618
00:40:14.710 --> 00:40:16.770
I'll get him!

619
00:40:20.410 --> 00:40:22.210
Very good.
Now come out of plough.

620
00:40:22.280 --> 00:40:24.440
Very nice.
Breathing. Good.

621
00:40:24.520 --> 00:40:27.880
Pull up under. Very nice.
Molly. out of plough.

622
00:40:27.950 --> 00:40:29.940
Come on. Molly.
Let's go.

623
00:40:30.020 --> 00:40:33.920
Could you please help me?
This is starting to hurt.

624
00:40:33.990 --> 00:40:35.590
Oh. my God.

625
00:40:35.660 --> 00:40:37.250
73... beautiful.

626
00:40:37.330 --> 00:40:38.560
74.

627
00:40:38.630 --> 00:40:40.000
75... very good.

628
00:40:40.070 --> 00:40:41.360
76.

629
00:40:41.430 --> 00:40:42.560
77...

630
00:40:42.640 --> 00:40:44.400
Let me put a few more on.

631
00:40:44.470 --> 00:40:46.230
Ing. here we go.

632
00:40:47.340 --> 00:40:48.600
Waist.

633
00:40:49.580 --> 00:40:52.840
Molly. you get to be in charge
of the chocolate chip cookies.

634
00:40:52.910 --> 00:40:55.070
They're already mixed.
so all you have to do

635
00:40:55.150 --> 00:40:57.240
is put them in the oven
and time them.

636
00:40:59.850 --> 00:41:01.080
Salmonella.

637
00:41:06.690 --> 00:41:08.680
You're letting her do this?

638
00:41:08.760 --> 00:41:10.730
Relax. girls.
It's just cookie mix.

639
00:41:10.800 --> 00:41:12.920
How badly
can she screw it up?

640
00:41:13.000 --> 00:41:14.590
Put it out now!
Put it out!

641
00:41:14.670 --> 00:41:16.860
I'm trying!

642
00:41:24.910 --> 00:41:27.710
Oh. gosh!
This is Neal's jacket!

643
00:41:28.910 --> 00:41:30.850
Put it out!
- Get it out!

644
00:41:30.920 --> 00:41:33.910
Take it back!

645
00:41:33.990 --> 00:41:36.250
Oh. my God!
- Take it back now!

646
00:41:36.320 --> 00:41:38.620
What are you doing. Ray?

647
00:41:41.190 --> 00:41:43.320
Have you gone mad?

648
00:41:43.400 --> 00:41:46.990
There is never. ever an excuse
for hitting another person.

649
00:41:47.070 --> 00:41:48.120
What's going on?

650
00:41:48.200 --> 00:41:51.140
She was laughing at me
because her "au pair"

651
00:41:51.200 --> 00:41:54.540
said that my new nanny
was a slutbag whore.

652
00:41:59.040 --> 00:42:00.510
Go!

653
00:42:22.030 --> 00:42:24.730
I'm sorry.
Sorry.

654
00:42:32.680 --> 00:42:34.010
You've reached Ingrid.

655
00:42:34.080 --> 00:42:36.380
Please leave your number
and the time of your call.

656
00:42:36.450 --> 00:42:38.210
Be specific.

657
00:42:38.280 --> 00:42:40.840
Hi. it's Neal calling for Molly.

658
00:42:40.920 --> 00:42:42.910
I hope this is
the right number.

659
00:42:48.250 --> 00:42:50.240
I love Ingrid
with all my heart

660
00:42:50.320 --> 00:42:53.120
and all her cute
Martha Stewart-wannabe friends.

661
00:42:53.190 --> 00:42:55.660
but it's a real estrogen-fest
over there.

662
00:42:55.720 --> 00:42:59.850
A girl needs a testosterone injection
every once in a while.

663
00:42:59.930 --> 00:43:01.950
Not that I think
of you that way.

664
00:43:02.030 --> 00:43:04.020
You're super-sensitive.

665
00:43:04.100 --> 00:43:05.590
Don't be a silly goose.

666
00:43:05.670 --> 00:43:07.860
Please let me
patronize the arts.

667
00:43:07.940 --> 00:43:09.870
Well. actually...

668
00:43:11.410 --> 00:43:13.400
I just signed a deal
with Schleine Records.

669
00:43:14.580 --> 00:43:16.940
Oh. my God.
What?

670
00:43:17.010 --> 00:43:21.350
Oh. my God!
Neal. that's incredible!

671
00:43:21.420 --> 00:43:24.720
That's amazing!
Why didn't you say anything?

672
00:43:25.250 --> 00:43:27.550
I would have. but this is
the first time tonight

673
00:43:27.620 --> 00:43:29.350
I've managed
to get a word in edgewise.

674
00:43:29.420 --> 00:43:30.480
I...

675
00:43:35.100 --> 00:43:37.330
So how did you seal the deal?

676
00:43:49.780 --> 00:43:53.370
I know this one.
This is the deep one.

677
00:44:30.390 --> 00:44:32.410
I guess I looked
deep down inside

678
00:44:32.490 --> 00:44:35.220
and... found that inner hook.

679
00:44:35.290 --> 00:44:37.280
You certainly did...

680
00:44:37.960 --> 00:44:40.550
... and that calls for...

681
00:44:41.630 --> 00:44:44.890
... an outer hook to go with it.

682
00:44:48.840 --> 00:44:51.930
What's that?
- Your lucky jacket.

683
00:44:53.440 --> 00:44:54.700
My lucky...

684
00:44:56.950 --> 00:44:59.880
What have you done to it?
- A few minor improvements.

685
00:44:59.950 --> 00:45:01.310
Improvements?
- Yeah.

686
00:45:01.380 --> 00:45:03.680
You mutilated it!
- No. I fixed it.

687
00:45:03.750 --> 00:45:07.410
Look how great this is. I told you
purple was your magic color.

688
00:45:07.490 --> 00:45:09.080
We have to talk.

689
00:45:09.160 --> 00:45:11.890
Those are the four
most hateful words in English.

690
00:45:11.960 --> 00:45:13.890
I can't see you anymore.

691
00:45:13.960 --> 00:45:16.660
I'm sorry about the jacket.
- It's not about the jacket.

692
00:45:16.730 --> 00:45:19.100
I just can't see you.

693
00:45:19.830 --> 00:45:21.030
That's all.

694
00:45:21.100 --> 00:45:24.770
Right. You just do
the rock star's daughter

695
00:45:24.840 --> 00:45:27.240
so you can tell
your pop star-wannabe mates.

696
00:45:27.310 --> 00:45:29.970
then ride off into the sunset
with your crummy guitar...

697
00:45:30.040 --> 00:45:33.170
It's not like that.
I'm just not in a place...

698
00:45:38.420 --> 00:45:41.680
Ray. can you
turn that down. please?

699
00:45:50.770 --> 00:45:52.760
Thank you.

700
00:45:57.970 --> 00:46:00.940
You're supposed to put
the cream in before the sugar.

701
00:46:01.010 --> 00:46:04.640
I'm not having cream.
I can't gain weight.

702
00:46:04.710 --> 00:46:07.010
My ballet recital
is Friday night. remember?

703
00:46:07.080 --> 00:46:10.210
Right. I remember.

704
00:46:11.220 --> 00:46:15.380
I invited you to afternoon tea.
The least you can do is be polite.

705
00:46:15.460 --> 00:46:18.080
Why are you buttering
my plastic scone?

706
00:46:18.730 --> 00:46:22.420
Why are plastic scones on the table
when we have real food?

707
00:46:24.170 --> 00:46:26.000
You thought they were cute.

708
00:46:28.440 --> 00:46:31.100
Are you still moping
over that disgusting guy?

709
00:46:34.180 --> 00:46:36.440
Other people
always let you down.

710
00:46:36.510 --> 00:46:39.140
Why don't you forget them
and do something for yourself?

711
00:46:39.210 --> 00:46:40.940
Like what?

712
00:46:41.020 --> 00:46:43.280
I don't know.
Something you're good at.

713
00:46:43.350 --> 00:46:45.250
And I don't mean shopping.

714
00:46:46.320 --> 00:46:48.950
Maybe some of us
aren't good at anything.

715
00:46:49.020 --> 00:46:51.390
Every grownup
is good at something.

716
00:46:52.660 --> 00:46:53.890
My bad.

717
00:46:53.960 --> 00:46:56.400
I don't see any grownups
around here.

718
00:46:57.100 --> 00:46:59.690
What's so great
about being a grownup anyway?

719
00:47:01.270 --> 00:47:03.070
So I can turn out like you?

720
00:47:03.140 --> 00:47:04.800
You're scared.

721
00:47:06.340 --> 00:47:09.540
Sometimes when Mu hears people
walking by outside the door.

722
00:47:09.610 --> 00:47:12.740
he gets this funny expression
and runs into the bathroom.

723
00:47:12.810 --> 00:47:15.040
like he thinks
they're coming to get him.

724
00:47:15.820 --> 00:47:17.880
That's how you look.

725
00:47:18.620 --> 00:47:19.950
Where are you going?

726
00:47:20.020 --> 00:47:22.390
If you refuse
to have a nice time with me.

727
00:47:22.460 --> 00:47:25.190
I'm going to have fun
by myself.

728
00:47:25.260 --> 00:47:29.390
Two hundred pliés isn't fun. Ray.
It's slave labor.

729
00:47:29.460 --> 00:47:32.900
Fundamentals are
the building blocks of fun.

730
00:47:32.970 --> 00:47:35.730
Right. I forgot.

731
00:47:35.800 --> 00:47:37.860
What is with
this music. anyway?

732
00:47:37.940 --> 00:47:40.500
It's like a soundtrack
to slit your wrists to.

733
00:47:40.580 --> 00:47:44.200
It happens to be Mozart.
- It happens to be depressing.

734
00:47:44.280 --> 00:47:48.980
If we're gonna have fun. we need
to listen to music that's fun.

735
00:47:58.330 --> 00:48:00.420
I hate to break it to you.

736
00:48:00.500 --> 00:48:05.190
but this junk is not music!

737
00:48:05.270 --> 00:48:08.170
But it sure is fun
to dance to!

738
00:48:19.910 --> 00:48:21.470
Cut it out!

739
00:48:21.550 --> 00:48:23.540
You look like a spastic hyena!

740
00:48:23.620 --> 00:48:27.380
What are you doing?
What is your problem?

741
00:48:27.460 --> 00:48:29.790
Let me go!

742
00:48:29.860 --> 00:48:31.720
What are you doing?

743
00:48:48.840 --> 00:48:50.470
Grow up.

744
00:48:55.750 --> 00:48:57.340
Where are you going now?

745
00:48:57.420 --> 00:49:00.250
I have about a million
last-minute errands to run

746
00:49:00.320 --> 00:49:03.380
and a date with this
normal adult guy I met.

747
00:49:03.460 --> 00:49:05.860
He's in computers.

748
00:49:05.930 --> 00:49:08.920
Ing. I am so sick
of all of these rock 'n' rollers.

749
00:49:09.000 --> 00:49:12.430
overpaid jocks.
and supermodel bitch boys.

750
00:49:14.900 --> 00:49:17.960
You know. I thought maybe.

751
00:49:18.040 --> 00:49:20.410
just maybe. you'd remember
we had plans tonight.

752
00:49:21.280 --> 00:49:25.270
Green tea tasting
at the Asia Society. remember?

753
00:49:27.550 --> 00:49:31.450
If I never have a drop of tea again.
it would be too soon.

754
00:49:31.520 --> 00:49:35.080
Please. go without me.
You'll have fun. Ing.

755
00:49:35.160 --> 00:49:36.920
I'm already a half-hour late.

756
00:49:36.990 --> 00:49:38.980
We were supposed
to go together.

757
00:49:39.060 --> 00:49:41.390
I RSVP'd over a month ago.

758
00:49:41.460 --> 00:49:43.560
It's too late
to invite anyone else.

759
00:49:43.630 --> 00:49:47.590
We're roomies. Ing.
That's why I pay half the rent.

760
00:49:48.340 --> 00:49:51.790
It doesn't mean I owe you
every minute of my free time.

761
00:49:51.870 --> 00:49:53.030
Owe me?

762
00:49:53.210 --> 00:49:58.800
You mean. for free yoga or nearly
burning down my apartment?

763
00:49:58.880 --> 00:50:01.850
Owe me? Is that what you
think of our friendship?

764
00:50:01.920 --> 00:50:06.110
Only because you think friendship
is having total control over my life.

765
00:50:06.190 --> 00:50:09.420
Unfortunately. you don't know
how to run your life. Molly.

766
00:50:09.490 --> 00:50:12.120
Fortunately.
that's not your problem.

767
00:50:12.860 --> 00:50:14.230
Not anymore.

768
00:50:19.630 --> 00:50:21.070
Look at you.

769
00:50:22.000 --> 00:50:25.770
You got rollers in your hair.
Is that your new style?

770
00:50:25.840 --> 00:50:27.770
I forgot.
I was in a hurry.

771
00:50:27.840 --> 00:50:29.330
Just playing.
Come here.

772
00:50:31.080 --> 00:50:32.710
Huey. my suitcases.

773
00:50:32.780 --> 00:50:34.110
My bad.

774
00:50:34.180 --> 00:50:36.880
Your room is that way.
Put your bags in there.

775
00:50:36.950 --> 00:50:38.510
I got your bed made up.

776
00:50:38.590 --> 00:50:40.710
Sorry. I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

777
00:50:40.790 --> 00:50:43.550
Okay. Thank you
for taking me in like this.

778
00:50:43.620 --> 00:50:47.250
Don't even trip. We all know
Ingrid can be a little anal.

779
00:50:47.330 --> 00:50:49.020
It's all good.
Besides...

780
00:50:49.100 --> 00:50:51.190
life with Huey
is one big party.

781
00:50:51.270 --> 00:50:55.290
Party time!

782
00:51:00.310 --> 00:51:02.640
That's what I'm talkin' about.

783
00:51:04.480 --> 00:51:06.140
Your turn.

784
00:51:21.300 --> 00:51:23.460
Bravo!

785
00:51:23.530 --> 00:51:25.560
Beautiful.

786
00:51:27.030 --> 00:51:28.020
Lovely.

787
00:51:36.040 --> 00:51:37.030
Yeah!

788
00:51:51.990 --> 00:51:53.550
Molly. no!

789
00:51:54.700 --> 00:51:56.090
Hi. Roma.

790
00:51:57.930 --> 00:51:59.830
It's me... Molly.

791
00:51:59.900 --> 00:52:02.270
Ray's nanny?

792
00:52:02.940 --> 00:52:04.730
Yes. of course.

793
00:52:04.810 --> 00:52:07.170
I was at your birthday party.
- Yeah.

794
00:52:07.240 --> 00:52:09.230
I'm a fan of your father's.

795
00:52:09.310 --> 00:52:11.540
He had that one song...
What was it?

796
00:52:11.610 --> 00:52:14.240
With your name in it.
- Yes.

797
00:52:14.320 --> 00:52:17.310
I was just wondering.
'cause it's my night off...

798
00:52:17.390 --> 00:52:18.850
who's watching Ray?

799
00:52:18.920 --> 00:52:21.510
She's at some
ballet thing or other.

800
00:52:21.590 --> 00:52:23.420
Oh. God.

801
00:52:23.490 --> 00:52:26.930
It's her recital?
I have to get over there.

802
00:52:26.990 --> 00:52:28.990
I'm sure it's over by now.

803
00:52:29.060 --> 00:52:31.430
I've arranged
to have a car pick her up. okay?

804
00:52:31.500 --> 00:52:32.990
Excuse me for a moment.

805
00:52:33.070 --> 00:52:34.430
I'm sorry.
Go ahead.

806
00:53:13.410 --> 00:53:16.000
Rise and shine. Ophelia.

807
00:53:16.080 --> 00:53:19.840
Hello. my little sugar pie.
How you doin'?

808
00:53:19.910 --> 00:53:22.110
Isn't it your day off?

809
00:53:22.750 --> 00:53:24.620
Indeed it is.

810
00:53:25.890 --> 00:53:27.380
And it's yours. too.

811
00:53:27.460 --> 00:53:32.190
No school. no homework.
and especially no fatal illnesses.

812
00:53:32.260 --> 00:53:33.420
Let me see this.

813
00:53:35.200 --> 00:53:37.290
Look at this.

814
00:53:37.370 --> 00:53:39.930
Perfect 98.6.

815
00:53:40.000 --> 00:53:42.700
only 20 degrees
above the temperature

816
00:53:42.770 --> 00:53:45.000
of the beautiful day
awaiting us.

817
00:53:45.070 --> 00:53:48.800
I'm not going anywhere.
especially with you.

818
00:53:48.880 --> 00:53:50.810
Oh. yes. you are.

819
00:53:53.780 --> 00:53:56.380
We are going to sit
in giant teacups

820
00:53:56.450 --> 00:54:00.150
and spin round and round
in circles until we puke.

821
00:54:00.220 --> 00:54:02.550
Are you on crack?

822
00:54:03.460 --> 00:54:04.950
We're gonna have fun.

823
00:54:10.230 --> 00:54:12.790
I can't believe
I let you talk me into this.

824
00:54:12.870 --> 00:54:15.560
You are gonna so love
Coney Island. Ray.

825
00:54:15.640 --> 00:54:18.700
Giant teacups you sit in.

826
00:54:18.770 --> 00:54:23.300
It's a ride. Ray.
like the ones at Disneyland.

827
00:54:25.650 --> 00:54:27.880
Haven't you ever been
to Disneyland?

828
00:54:29.850 --> 00:54:33.340
You've never been to Disneyland?
- Why don't you alert the media?

829
00:54:33.420 --> 00:54:37.820
Haven't you ever been
to an amusement park... ever?

830
00:54:38.930 --> 00:54:40.450
Oh. my God!

831
00:54:41.460 --> 00:54:44.330
Ray. you are so psyched!
- Whatever!

832
00:54:45.370 --> 00:54:48.630
Say it. Ray.
Say. "I am so psyched."

833
00:54:48.700 --> 00:54:50.690
I'm psyched. okay?

834
00:54:51.610 --> 00:54:53.900
Then you're gonna
have to pay the toll.

835
00:54:53.970 --> 00:54:55.970
It's like passing
through the gates

836
00:54:56.040 --> 00:54:58.200
before you can get
into the Emerald City.

837
00:54:58.280 --> 00:55:00.370
Let me go.
Are you trying to murder me?

838
00:55:00.450 --> 00:55:03.010
You have to eat one.
or they're not gonna let you in.

839
00:55:03.080 --> 00:55:05.070
They're toxic. you maniac.

840
00:55:05.150 --> 00:55:07.140
They have dead rats
and nitrates.

841
00:55:07.220 --> 00:55:11.210
Do you want to ride
the Spinning Teacups or not?

842
00:55:23.870 --> 00:55:25.360
Now swallow.

843
00:55:26.010 --> 00:55:27.670
Swallow.

844
00:55:34.620 --> 00:55:35.980
Wait.

845
00:55:42.120 --> 00:55:44.180
She's alive.

846
00:55:44.260 --> 00:55:45.590
She's alive!

847
00:55:45.660 --> 00:55:48.490
The operation was a success.
ladies and gentlemen!

848
00:55:48.560 --> 00:55:50.120
She's alive!

849
00:56:09.480 --> 00:56:10.850
Excuse me.

850
00:56:10.920 --> 00:56:13.180
Why is it so dead around here?

851
00:56:13.250 --> 00:56:16.660
The rides don't run
till the season starts.

852
00:56:16.720 --> 00:56:18.590
The season?

853
00:56:19.160 --> 00:56:21.290
You're a week early.

854
00:56:22.660 --> 00:56:24.100
Thanks.

855
00:57:17.550 --> 00:57:19.250
Let's go home.

856
00:57:36.440 --> 00:57:41.200
The last time I saw my mom
and dad. I was eight going on nine...

857
00:57:41.280 --> 00:57:44.540
eight years. six months.
and three days.

858
00:57:44.610 --> 00:57:47.240
almost as old as you are.

859
00:57:47.310 --> 00:57:51.380
They were going on tour.
leaving me behind for the first time.

860
00:57:51.450 --> 00:57:53.980
They didn't want me
missing any more school.

861
00:57:54.050 --> 00:57:56.320
When they came to my room
to say good-bye.

862
00:57:56.390 --> 00:58:00.220
I wouldn't open the door.
so they left.

863
00:58:00.290 --> 00:58:02.060
I fell asleep.

864
00:58:02.900 --> 00:58:04.920
The next thing I knew...

865
00:58:05.870 --> 00:58:08.460
my nanny was waking me up
in the middle of the night

866
00:58:08.540 --> 00:58:11.060
telling me
their plane had crashed.

867
00:58:11.140 --> 00:58:13.540
You're lucky.
- Lucky?

868
00:58:13.610 --> 00:58:15.510
That you were mad.

869
00:58:16.340 --> 00:58:19.040
When you're mad.
you don't miss people.

870
00:58:19.110 --> 00:58:22.640
and if you stay mad.
it's like you never knew them at all.

871
00:58:22.720 --> 00:58:25.310
That way you don't
have to feel sucky about it.

872
00:58:25.890 --> 00:58:27.480
You were lucky.

873
00:58:30.490 --> 00:58:31.620
Night.

874
00:58:33.960 --> 00:58:36.020
I wasn't mad. Ray.

875
00:58:37.630 --> 00:58:39.790
I was confused.

876
00:58:40.470 --> 00:58:42.700
Everyone was talking to me.

877
00:58:42.770 --> 00:58:45.530
and I couldn't understand
a word they were saying.

878
00:58:47.370 --> 00:58:49.970
Then their voices
became a blur...

879
00:58:51.010 --> 00:58:53.980
and soon I couldn't even
recognize their faces.

880
00:58:55.020 --> 00:58:57.140
They were like these blobs.

881
00:58:58.390 --> 00:59:00.850
Then they started
to grow fangs...

882
00:59:01.860 --> 00:59:04.050
and their eyes
became green.

883
00:59:05.190 --> 00:59:07.390
I knew I had to run away.

884
00:59:09.430 --> 00:59:11.420
I packed my knapsack.

885
00:59:11.500 --> 00:59:15.160
got on the train.
looked up at the map.

886
00:59:15.240 --> 00:59:18.670
and decided that I wanted
to live in Coney Island.

887
00:59:19.540 --> 00:59:23.500
I thought
it was gonna be a real island...

888
00:59:24.680 --> 00:59:29.080
and I could hide away there like
Tom Sawyer and Huckleberry Finn.

889
00:59:29.150 --> 00:59:31.520
Imagine my surprise.

890
00:59:31.590 --> 00:59:35.080
The Teacups was the only ride
they'd let me on by myself.

891
00:59:35.160 --> 00:59:40.460
I got on it and started
spinning myself round and round.

892
00:59:41.230 --> 00:59:43.590
I feel like I'm still there.

893
00:59:43.660 --> 00:59:46.630
spinning round
and round and round.

894
00:59:46.700 --> 00:59:49.230
and the ride won't stop.

895
00:59:49.300 --> 00:59:51.770
and I won't dare get off.

896
00:59:54.110 --> 00:59:56.100
You were right. Ray.

897
01:00:04.280 --> 01:00:06.220
I am scared.

898
01:00:09.460 --> 01:00:11.190
But you're scared. too.

899
01:00:12.390 --> 01:00:14.660
You're as scared as I am.

900
01:00:14.730 --> 01:00:17.200
and I thought maybe...

901
01:00:18.200 --> 01:00:20.220
I thought maybe if we...

902
01:00:21.100 --> 01:00:23.300
could go together...

903
01:01:23.700 --> 01:01:25.860
Morning. cutie.

904
01:01:26.630 --> 01:01:28.190
You hungry?

905
01:01:48.090 --> 01:01:50.080
You're up a little early.

906
01:01:59.130 --> 01:02:01.120
What are you doing here?

907
01:02:02.370 --> 01:02:04.960
I happen to work here.

908
01:02:05.040 --> 01:02:06.530
What are you doing?

909
01:02:06.610 --> 01:02:08.730
Don't forget the sugar. sugar!

910
01:03:08.140 --> 01:03:09.860
Just breathe.

911
01:03:19.380 --> 01:03:21.110
Lady!

912
01:03:21.920 --> 01:03:25.210
Lady. that water
is contaminated. you know.

913
01:03:25.290 --> 01:03:27.480
You better get out of there.

914
01:03:27.550 --> 01:03:29.780
That's pure sewage
you're in. there.

915
01:03:30.660 --> 01:03:33.220
Did you hear me?
Did you hear me?

916
01:03:33.290 --> 01:03:36.060
Yeah. I heard you!
- That water's filthy!

917
01:03:36.130 --> 01:03:38.220
If you don't get out.
I'll call the police.

918
01:03:38.300 --> 01:03:40.100
I'm getting out.

919
01:03:55.350 --> 01:03:57.440
A hundred and one degrees.

920
01:03:58.190 --> 01:03:59.680
Sick as a dog.

921
01:03:59.750 --> 01:04:02.090
You better hope
you don't get radiation poisoning

922
01:04:02.160 --> 01:04:04.520
from that toxic pond scum.

923
01:04:04.590 --> 01:04:06.990
Take two Echinacea

924
01:04:07.060 --> 01:04:10.090
and a Benadryl
for your sinuses.

925
01:04:10.160 --> 01:04:12.500
Okay.
- Call me if you need anything else.

926
01:04:12.570 --> 01:04:14.430
Stay here. Mu.

927
01:04:17.670 --> 01:04:19.430
Where are you going?

928
01:04:19.510 --> 01:04:21.100
I don't know.

929
01:04:21.170 --> 01:04:23.070
Maybe the library.

930
01:04:24.850 --> 01:04:26.840
Is that where you went
last night?

931
01:04:28.150 --> 01:04:29.640
I'm not gonna bother him.

932
01:04:29.720 --> 01:04:32.740
I'm just gonna sit quietly
and read or something.

933
01:04:33.490 --> 01:04:35.790
You can read out loud.

934
01:04:35.860 --> 01:04:37.620
I think he might like that.

935
01:04:37.690 --> 01:04:39.960
He's a vegetable. Molly.

936
01:04:40.030 --> 01:04:44.160
Chatting it up with my dad isn't
gonna do anyone any good at all.

937
01:04:44.230 --> 01:04:45.790
You're the doctor.

938
01:04:45.870 --> 01:04:48.230
It's not gonna do any good.

939
01:04:48.300 --> 01:04:51.200
I saw this show once on TV

940
01:04:51.270 --> 01:04:53.600
about all these sick people.

941
01:04:53.670 --> 01:04:58.080
The ones where their friends
and families talked to them

942
01:04:58.150 --> 01:05:02.450
held on ten times longer
than the ones left all alone.

943
01:05:02.520 --> 01:05:05.950
and that is a fact.

944
01:05:09.460 --> 01:05:11.360
Do you swear?

945
01:05:12.530 --> 01:05:14.020
I swear.

946
01:05:15.330 --> 01:05:16.960
Pinky promise?

947
01:05:18.270 --> 01:05:19.630
Don't touch.

948
01:05:20.770 --> 01:05:24.200
Germs. Sorry.
- Germs. Right.

949
01:05:28.410 --> 01:05:30.100
Wanna come?

950
01:05:37.820 --> 01:05:39.650
Can I help you
with something?

951
01:05:39.720 --> 01:05:43.250
She's going to go talk to him
for a little while.

952
01:05:43.320 --> 01:05:45.620
You know... privately?

953
01:05:48.600 --> 01:05:50.930
I can't think of what to say.

954
01:05:51.000 --> 01:05:53.520
There's an all-time first.

955
01:06:08.010 --> 01:06:09.540
Hey. Dad.

956
01:06:10.620 --> 01:06:12.710
I know I haven't...

957
01:06:13.920 --> 01:06:18.580
Well. what I really wanted
to tell you was about my new pet.

958
01:06:18.660 --> 01:06:20.790
It's really Molly's.
my nanny.

959
01:06:20.860 --> 01:06:24.160
but the thing is.

960
01:06:24.230 --> 01:06:28.000
it's a pig... literally.

961
01:06:28.070 --> 01:06:30.660
His name is Mu.

962
01:06:30.740 --> 01:06:32.830
He's from Thailand.

963
01:06:32.910 --> 01:06:35.530
He's really clean.
I have to admit.

964
01:06:35.610 --> 01:06:37.700
even if he is a pig.

965
01:06:41.780 --> 01:06:45.810
Anyway. what I'm really into
these days is ballet.

966
01:06:45.890 --> 01:06:49.520
You and Mom used to say
that it was old-fashioned.

967
01:06:49.590 --> 01:06:51.780
but I swear it's really cool.

968
01:06:51.860 --> 01:06:54.880
I'm already doing
changements and chaînèes...

969
01:06:54.960 --> 01:06:57.930
you know. when you spin
and spin and spin.

970
01:06:58.000 --> 01:06:59.830
It used to make me dizzy.

971
01:06:59.900 --> 01:07:02.370
Now I'm only dizzy when I stop.

972
01:07:17.150 --> 01:07:20.920
What a one-hit wonder
that slut turned out to be.

973
01:07:20.990 --> 01:07:23.220
It's his first single.
It just dropped.

974
01:07:23.290 --> 01:07:26.920
It's been playing in my head
for weeks. and it sucks.

975
01:07:26.990 --> 01:07:28.320
What is this?

976
01:07:28.400 --> 01:07:31.090
This is so '80s
it makes my hair pouf.

977
01:07:31.800 --> 01:07:33.320
Hold up. Listen.

978
01:07:33.400 --> 01:07:36.560
I produced this video.
and the '80s are back.

979
01:07:36.640 --> 01:07:38.300
I don't know
where you've been.

980
01:07:38.370 --> 01:07:41.900
Listening to Tchaikovsky.
Mozart. and Chopin.

981
01:07:41.980 --> 01:07:46.170
You wouldn't know real music if I
hit you on the head with it. Gooey.

982
01:07:47.380 --> 01:07:49.540
You're gonna stop
calling me Gooey.

983
01:07:49.620 --> 01:07:50.980
So?

984
01:07:52.350 --> 01:07:55.380
What do you think?
- What is it?

985
01:07:55.460 --> 01:07:57.750
It's a tutu. silly.

986
01:07:57.820 --> 01:07:59.550
For what. a midget?

987
01:07:59.630 --> 01:08:02.600
No. for a little girl
named Ray.

988
01:08:02.660 --> 01:08:04.990
Her year-end dance recital
is coming up.

989
01:08:05.070 --> 01:08:07.730
The costumes are so boring.
I figured I'd surprise her

990
01:08:07.800 --> 01:08:10.130
with something
pretty spectacular.

991
01:08:21.950 --> 01:08:23.850
He's wearing the jacket!

992
01:08:23.920 --> 01:08:26.680
That's my jacket!
I made that jacket!

993
01:08:28.990 --> 01:08:30.790
That was my idea!

994
01:08:38.700 --> 01:08:41.600
He is the Lizard King
Reincarnated.

995
01:08:43.570 --> 01:08:45.560
No. listen to me.
Look at me.

996
01:08:48.380 --> 01:08:50.340
I'm the lizard king.

997
01:08:50.410 --> 01:08:52.710
This guy. he's nothing
but an illusion.

998
01:08:52.780 --> 01:08:56.240
He ain't real.
Everything he is. I made.

999
01:08:56.320 --> 01:08:59.310
You want real.
you want substance.

1000
01:08:59.390 --> 01:09:01.980
look no further
than what you got in front of you.

1001
01:09:02.060 --> 01:09:04.550
I'm the lizard king.

1002
01:09:06.730 --> 01:09:08.720
You're right. Huey.

1003
01:09:08.800 --> 01:09:11.090
True friends. true hearts.

1004
01:09:11.160 --> 01:09:13.500
That is what counts in life.

1005
01:09:13.570 --> 01:09:16.590
That's right.
Hit me one.

1006
01:09:16.670 --> 01:09:18.640
Give me some love.

1007
01:09:21.070 --> 01:09:23.870
That's funny.
I wasn't expecting anyone.

1008
01:09:23.940 --> 01:09:25.640
Go see who it is.

1009
01:09:30.650 --> 01:09:32.210
Hey. man.

1010
01:09:32.290 --> 01:09:34.150
What's going on?

1011
01:09:40.390 --> 01:09:42.660
Hi. 81st and 5th. please.

1012
01:09:57.440 --> 01:10:00.640
When did it happen?
- He passed away this afternoon.

1013
01:10:18.400 --> 01:10:20.420
I'm so sorry.

1014
01:10:31.640 --> 01:10:33.270
You promised.

1015
01:10:38.120 --> 01:10:41.710
Miss Gunn. Mrs. Schleine
is waiting for you in the study.

1016
01:10:46.230 --> 01:10:49.290
I'm so sorry. Mrs. Schleine.
- Thanks for coming. Miss Gunn.

1017
01:10:49.360 --> 01:10:51.060
Are you kidding?

1018
01:10:51.130 --> 01:10:53.360
Nothing could keep me away
at a time like this.

1019
01:10:53.430 --> 01:10:55.870
Last week's pay
and a month's severance.

1020
01:10:57.670 --> 01:10:59.100
Severance?

1021
01:10:59.170 --> 01:11:01.070
We're letting you go.

1022
01:11:03.140 --> 01:11:04.370
"We"?

1023
01:11:04.440 --> 01:11:06.570
That's right.
Me and Ray.

1024
01:11:06.650 --> 01:11:09.950
We.
Good night. Miss Gunn.

1025
01:11:12.790 --> 01:11:16.690
I'm sorry. but I'm not leaving
without an explanation.

1026
01:11:20.630 --> 01:11:23.190
I don't know what's been going on
between you and my daughter.

1027
01:11:23.260 --> 01:11:26.030
but she has made it clear
she never wants to see you again.

1028
01:11:26.100 --> 01:11:28.970
She must be going
out of her mind with grief.

1029
01:11:29.040 --> 01:11:31.270
Actually. she's taking it
rather well.

1030
01:11:31.340 --> 01:11:35.000
I was at my staff meeting when I
got the news about my husband.

1031
01:11:35.070 --> 01:11:37.980
I came home to find Ray
finishing her homework.

1032
01:11:38.040 --> 01:11:41.880
She's been very calm
and level-headed about this whole affair.

1033
01:11:43.350 --> 01:11:45.750
You call that taking it well?

1034
01:11:47.320 --> 01:11:50.760
Do you know what ètage
your daughter's at in ballet?

1035
01:11:52.390 --> 01:11:54.720
Or that she was banned
from her science class

1036
01:11:54.790 --> 01:11:59.090
for stealing a formaldehyde pig
so she could give it a proper burial?

1037
01:11:59.630 --> 01:12:01.570
The tea set you got her...

1038
01:12:01.630 --> 01:12:04.540
it's exquisite and beautiful.

1039
01:12:04.600 --> 01:12:07.000
but do you know
how she likes to have her tea.

1040
01:12:07.070 --> 01:12:09.670
how many lumps...
one. two... cream. sugar?

1041
01:12:09.740 --> 01:12:11.900
And the point
of your little tirade is...

1042
01:12:11.980 --> 01:12:13.140
You're right.

1043
01:12:14.180 --> 01:12:17.240
You don't know what goes on
between me and Ray

1044
01:12:17.320 --> 01:12:21.520
because you don't know very much
about your own daughter.

1045
01:12:21.590 --> 01:12:24.820
I know my daughter well enough
to respect her wishes.

1046
01:12:26.930 --> 01:12:29.050
You don't give her respect.

1047
01:12:29.130 --> 01:12:32.930
You give her whatever she asks for
so you don't have to deal with her.

1048
01:12:34.800 --> 01:12:36.630
She's eight years old.

1049
01:12:37.670 --> 01:12:39.730
She is not 28.

1050
01:12:43.510 --> 01:12:47.110
Please remember that the next time
you show her some "respect."

1051
01:12:57.790 --> 01:13:01.280
It's my muse.
- Getting in your way again.

1052
01:13:04.300 --> 01:13:06.290
Molly. I came here to see you.

1053
01:13:07.330 --> 01:13:08.660
For what?

1054
01:13:09.570 --> 01:13:12.500
I haven't been able to write
a single decent song

1055
01:13:12.570 --> 01:13:14.670
since we last saw each other.

1056
01:13:16.040 --> 01:13:19.840
Molly. I'm sorry. I was trying
to take a step forward.

1057
01:13:19.910 --> 01:13:22.210
but I took two steps
backward instead.

1058
01:13:22.280 --> 01:13:23.910
Why don't you take
one step sideways?

1059
01:13:23.980 --> 01:13:26.920
Then we can stop doing
this silly little dance.

1060
01:13:29.060 --> 01:13:31.290
So that's the Molly M.O.

1061
01:13:31.360 --> 01:13:33.660
When I'm not ready.
you hunt me down.

1062
01:13:33.730 --> 01:13:36.290
When I try and make it work.
you're not interested.

1063
01:13:38.730 --> 01:13:42.460
Ever since we met.
it's about what I'm doing wrong...

1064
01:13:43.700 --> 01:13:45.930
but I'm not the one
with the problem.

1065
01:13:46.010 --> 01:13:49.340
You are.
you and your selfishness.

1066
01:13:49.410 --> 01:13:51.740
All you do is take.

1067
01:13:52.710 --> 01:13:55.940
I've got nothing for you
right now. so...

1068
01:13:56.020 --> 01:13:59.780
maybe it's time to start thinking
about someone other than yourself.

1069
01:13:59.850 --> 01:14:01.150
Till then...

1070
01:14:11.100 --> 01:14:12.930
Good morning.
ladies and gentlemen.

1071
01:14:13.270 --> 01:14:16.100
Now we'll start the bidding
on this important collection

1072
01:14:16.170 --> 01:14:19.730
representing a vital chapter
in American musical history.

1073
01:14:19.810 --> 01:14:23.640
Tommy Gunn was an essential
member of several landmark bands.

1074
01:14:23.710 --> 01:14:25.540
He scored a solo hit
with "Molly Smiles"...

1075
01:14:25.610 --> 01:14:28.980
Maybe we should wait a few minutes
till everyone shows up.

1076
01:14:29.050 --> 01:14:32.750
I'm afraid this is about as good
as it's going to get.

1077
01:14:32.820 --> 01:14:35.120
We have here Tommy Gunn's
signature acoustic.

1078
01:14:35.190 --> 01:14:38.020
which he played with his first band
in Haight-Ashbury.

1079
01:14:38.090 --> 01:14:41.620
Bidding starts at $2.500.
Do I hear $2.500?

1080
01:14:41.690 --> 01:14:43.690
2.500.
- I have $2.500.

1081
01:14:43.760 --> 01:14:45.660
Do I hear $2.600?
- 2.500?

1082
01:14:45.730 --> 01:14:47.320
2.600.
- Thank you.

1083
01:14:47.400 --> 01:14:48.730
2.500?

1084
01:14:48.800 --> 01:14:52.100
I'm sorry. We put out feelers.
but unfortunately

1085
01:14:52.170 --> 01:14:55.070
the excitement generated
by Mr. Gunn's memorabilia

1086
01:14:55.140 --> 01:14:58.200
fell somewhat short
of expectations.

1087
01:14:58.280 --> 01:14:59.370
I have 3.000.

1088
01:14:59.450 --> 01:15:01.470
3.000 going once.

1089
01:15:01.550 --> 01:15:02.980
3.000 going twice...

1090
01:15:03.050 --> 01:15:06.750
75.000!
I have an offer of 75.000...

1091
01:15:06.820 --> 01:15:09.340
from a buyer who wishes
to remain anonymous...

1092
01:15:09.420 --> 01:15:11.480
for the entire collection.

1093
01:15:17.700 --> 01:15:20.530
Well? What do you say?

1094
01:15:21.700 --> 01:15:23.460
It's up to you.

1095
01:15:24.170 --> 01:15:27.230
Frankly. I can't envision
a much better result

1096
01:15:27.310 --> 01:15:29.370
from selling it off piecemeal.

1097
01:15:29.980 --> 01:15:33.910
This is everything that he's
left behind in the whole world.

1098
01:15:36.750 --> 01:15:38.740
This is my dad.

1099
01:15:39.520 --> 01:15:40.710
I'm sorry.

1100
01:15:46.990 --> 01:15:49.290
Just get rid of it.

1101
01:15:58.140 --> 01:15:59.600
Molly. where are you taking me?

1102
01:16:01.710 --> 01:16:03.940
The fellas are waiting for us
at the club.

1103
01:16:04.010 --> 01:16:06.810
The fellas can wait. Huey.

1104
01:16:06.880 --> 01:16:08.610
This is important.

1105
01:16:08.680 --> 01:16:11.670
Hold up.
Molly. please.

1106
01:16:11.750 --> 01:16:14.350
They better have
a defibrillator up there.

1107
01:16:14.420 --> 01:16:17.510
Gooey. suck it up.
It's good for your heinie.

1108
01:16:18.320 --> 01:16:21.590
Welcome
to Le Château Chez Molly.

1109
01:16:26.300 --> 01:16:28.560
This is...
- It's my new apartment.

1110
01:16:28.630 --> 01:16:31.830
This way is the kitchen area.

1111
01:16:31.900 --> 01:16:33.900
and over here
in this direction.

1112
01:16:33.970 --> 01:16:38.240
you'll find the very private.
secluded bathroom section.

1113
01:16:38.310 --> 01:16:40.140
Fabulous. huh?

1114
01:16:40.210 --> 01:16:43.550
You're standing in the living room.
which. coincidentally.

1115
01:16:43.620 --> 01:16:45.170
happens to be...

1116
01:16:47.320 --> 01:16:48.750
the bedroom.

1117
01:16:49.720 --> 01:16:51.310
It's got potential. huh?

1118
01:16:51.390 --> 01:16:53.980
As a detention cell
for convicted felons. maybe.

1119
01:16:54.060 --> 01:16:56.490
Molly. this isn't you.

1120
01:16:56.560 --> 01:16:58.830
I can't afford me
anymore. Huey.

1121
01:16:58.900 --> 01:17:01.660
Nobody's kicking you out.
You can still stay with me.

1122
01:17:01.730 --> 01:17:06.540
I really have to stand on
my own two feet right now. okay?

1123
01:17:07.140 --> 01:17:08.130
Okay.

1124
01:17:11.680 --> 01:17:13.080
Hello?

1125
01:17:15.250 --> 01:17:18.050
Roma. how would I know
where Ray is?

1126
01:17:19.890 --> 01:17:21.880
What's going on with Ray?

1127
01:17:21.950 --> 01:17:23.440
Hold on one second.

1128
01:17:24.460 --> 01:17:25.520
Thanks.

1129
01:17:25.590 --> 01:17:28.420
Roma? Hi.
It's Molly.

1130
01:17:28.490 --> 01:17:32.160
Miss Gunn. I know
that you've been let go.

1131
01:17:32.230 --> 01:17:36.860
but is there any chance that
you've seen my daughter today?

1132
01:17:38.340 --> 01:17:39.930
Are you sure?

1133
01:17:41.910 --> 01:17:44.040
Ray didn't come home
from school.

1134
01:17:44.110 --> 01:17:46.100
She's been missing ever since.

1135
01:17:46.180 --> 01:17:48.170
I thought
that she might have...

1136
01:17:49.980 --> 01:17:52.380
If you hear from her.
please let me know.

1137
01:17:53.220 --> 01:17:55.020
Huey. talk to her.

1138
01:18:06.200 --> 01:18:08.960
You all right?
- I'm fine. thanks.

1139
01:20:41.490 --> 01:20:43.480
It's nice to see you again.
- You. too.

1140
01:20:43.560 --> 01:20:45.550
I really miss you.
- I miss you.

1141
01:20:46.090 --> 01:20:47.990
These are crummy circumstances.

1142
01:20:48.060 --> 01:20:49.580
Molly Gunn?
- Yeah.

1143
01:20:49.660 --> 01:20:51.150
How you doin'?
- Good.

1144
01:20:51.230 --> 01:20:53.200
Good to meet you.
- Same here.

1145
01:20:53.270 --> 01:20:56.960
I saw that kid Neal Fox's video.
Didn't you create his look?

1146
01:20:57.040 --> 01:20:59.900
No. I just fixed his jacket.

1147
01:20:59.970 --> 01:21:02.410
I don't know why
everybody's talking about it.

1148
01:21:02.480 --> 01:21:04.470
Do you do pants. too?

1149
01:21:04.540 --> 01:21:06.980
Cool leather ones
that aren't over the top?

1150
01:21:07.050 --> 01:21:09.240
I'm hoping you can hook me up
with a jacket.

1151
01:21:09.320 --> 01:21:11.840
Not the same one. obviously.
but with a similar vibe.

1152
01:21:11.920 --> 01:21:14.390
Guys. thank you.
You're very sweet.

1153
01:21:14.450 --> 01:21:17.620
It was sort of
a big accident. yeah.

1154
01:21:17.690 --> 01:21:20.450
It's a hell of an accident.
What do you think?

1155
01:21:25.030 --> 01:21:26.460
I would love to.
- Cool.

1156
01:21:26.530 --> 01:21:28.230
Done.
- Pants. too.

1157
01:21:28.300 --> 01:21:30.700
Guys. Garth Brooks
wants to meet you.

1158
01:21:30.770 --> 01:21:32.640
You're kidding.
- He's over there.

1159
01:21:32.710 --> 01:21:35.170
Excuse us. Mr. Brooks?
- Okay. Yeah.

1160
01:21:35.240 --> 01:21:37.270
Let's go.
- Awesome.

1161
01:22:11.110 --> 01:22:12.130
Thanks.

1162
01:22:16.620 --> 01:22:19.240
No. that's yours.

1163
01:22:19.320 --> 01:22:22.480
Molly. I just spoke with her.

1164
01:22:22.560 --> 01:22:24.920
She's almost ready
to meet with people.

1165
01:22:24.990 --> 01:22:27.890
but she wants
to talk to you first.

1166
01:22:36.140 --> 01:22:38.700
You can have
your job back. you know.

1167
01:22:39.770 --> 01:22:41.670
I don't think so.

1168
01:22:42.370 --> 01:22:43.860
You and I...

1169
01:22:45.110 --> 01:22:47.410
we're gonna be friends.

1170
01:22:47.480 --> 01:22:48.850
Okay?

1171
01:22:51.280 --> 01:22:54.180
Grownups never stay friends
with kids.

1172
01:22:55.520 --> 01:22:58.050
I don't see any grownups
around here.

1173
01:23:00.590 --> 01:23:02.080
I do.

1174
01:23:05.560 --> 01:23:08.090
You know the Dalai Lama?

1175
01:23:09.000 --> 01:23:12.130
I've always thought of myself
as a people person.

1176
01:23:12.200 --> 01:23:16.440
Most Fashion Institute applicants
would kill for references like yours.

1177
01:23:16.510 --> 01:23:18.500
Seems to me
you could skip school

1178
01:23:18.580 --> 01:23:21.070
and find work with one
of your designer friends.

1179
01:23:21.150 --> 01:23:24.480
It would be more fun than
toiling away here for four years.

1180
01:23:24.550 --> 01:23:27.780
Fundamentals are
the building blocks of fun...

1181
01:23:30.190 --> 01:23:31.820
I always say.

1182
01:23:33.130 --> 01:23:34.290
Oh. God.

1183
01:23:38.660 --> 01:23:40.220
Man. she's gonna kill me.

1184
01:23:40.300 --> 01:23:42.460
I'm really sorry.

1185
01:23:42.540 --> 01:23:44.630
Okay. Sorry.

1186
01:23:44.700 --> 01:23:47.540
Please call me
and I will call you.

1187
01:23:47.610 --> 01:23:50.040
and thank you.

1188
01:23:50.110 --> 01:23:52.170
Have a great day. Bye.

1189
01:23:53.250 --> 01:23:56.310
She always does this to me.
She's not coming.

1190
01:23:57.180 --> 01:23:59.170
If you'd quit wiggling your ass.

1191
01:23:59.250 --> 01:24:01.520
it wouldn't have fallen off
in the first place.

1192
01:24:10.460 --> 01:24:11.830
Coming through.

1193
01:24:13.600 --> 01:24:14.590
Excuse me.

1194
01:24:18.670 --> 01:24:21.770
To conclude our program.
we present a special performance...

1195
01:24:21.840 --> 01:24:24.140
Are you okay?
- By Laraine Schleine.

1196
01:24:33.250 --> 01:24:35.080
And to accompany Miss Schleine.

1197
01:24:35.150 --> 01:24:39.090
we are pleased to present
a very special guest.

1198
01:24:59.910 --> 01:25:01.380
How's it going?

1199
01:25:04.520 --> 01:25:07.820
There's someone here today
who lent us a bit of her magic.

1200
01:25:07.890 --> 01:25:11.790
and now we'd like
to give some of it back.

1201
01:25:14.390 --> 01:25:16.380
This was Tommy Gunn's
favorite guitar.

1202
01:25:16.460 --> 01:25:19.120
and I'm going to sing you
the song he wrote

1203
01:25:19.200 --> 01:25:21.860
for his favorite person
in the world.

1204
01:25:22.940 --> 01:25:25.170
This one goes out
to Molly Gunn.

1205
01:28:17.240 --> 01:28:19.770
Every story has an end.

1206
01:28:19.850 --> 01:28:21.540
but in life.

1207
01:28:21.610 --> 01:28:23.980
every ending
is just a new beginning.

1208
01:28:24.050 --> 01:28:32.860
Nothing's wrong
when Molly smiles

1209
01:28:40.000 --> 01:28:50.000
